Infrastructure Destroyed, Damaged in Japan's March 11 Earthquake, Tsunami

-- B y   J a e   H u r
-- 
2011-03-27T02:32:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/infrastructure-destroyed-damaged-in-japan-s-march-11-earthquake-tsunami.html
A total of 135,563 buildings were
destroyed or damaged, and 2,142 roads damaged, in the magnitude-
9.0 earthquake and tsunami that hit  Japan  on March 11. The data
come from  statistics  compiled on the website of  National Police
Agency  as of 10 a.m. today.  Buildings Destroyed or Damaged  ==========================================================
Prefecture          Roads             Bridges  Damaged           Destroyed
==========================================================  Aomori                 2  Iwate                 26                 4  Miyagi               966                10  Akita                  9  Yamagata              15  Tokyo                 16                 1  Ibaraki              307                41  Tochigi              257  Gunma                  7  Saitama              160  Chiba                321  ------------------------------------------------------------
Total               2086                56 